The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Mumbai, Jan. 1: An alleged blood-loving assassin who left a beer can after battering his poor victims with sticks and stabbing them repeatedly was sentenced to life in prison today.           Ravindra Kantrole, known as Beer Man, was sentenced in one of the three cases slapped on him for stabbing a man 20 times in his chest, abdomen, arms and thighs on a bridge near Marine Drive on January 11, 2007.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Omar Abdullah has announced that his party, the National Conference, will join the UPA. He said his party would write to UPA chairperson Sonia Gandhi, the Lok Sabha and the Rajya Sabha chairman on this. Omar will be sworn in Jammu and Kashmir chief minister on January 5.                  
	 Kuala Lumpur (PTI): An Indian has been sentenced to 12 years imprisonment for murdering his Malaysian employer. Nagarajan Vaithilingam, 22, from Tamil Nadu had claimed he had been sexually abused by his employer Ganthi Kanapathy, 33, who owned the barber shop. Two other Indian accused were acquitted after he pleaded guilty.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Rajiv Mathur took over as the new director of the Intelligence Bureau on Thursday. Mathur, who is considered an expert in handling Northeast insurgencies and has served the bureau for nearly three decades, will succeed P.C. Haldar.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): India has suffered losses of over Rs 100,000 crore in flood damage between 1953 and2007, according to a report by the Working Group on Water Resources. It added that Rs 12, 362 crore had been spent till the end of the Eleventh Five Year Plan.                   
	 Jammu (PTI): A 20-year-old girl has allegedly crossed over to Pakistan-occupied Kashmir to meet her mother, officials said on Thursday. Niseera Bi went missing from a village in Poonch district close to the Line of Control on Wednesday.
                                                                                                                           
